And the descendants of Montezuma are filled with belligerence.
Mexico's most difficult relationship with more than 35 million Mexican Americans living in the United States is.
You want to talk about insults?
That's enough.
There are winners and losers in Mexico, people who find opportunities in Mexico, and those who don't.
In L.A., Las Vegas, Phoenix, Denver or San Antonio, so many people of Mexican origin had only one reason: at some point in their family history, someone — father or grandfather — had no opportunity to realize himself in Mexico and had to go north.
Most of the time, they were Mexicans of a certain type -- smug, under-educated, of poor peasant families.
We're their descendants, and we remember that.
Mexico sees it differently.
Today our lives are the embodiment of the American dream, we've studied in good schools, and we've done good work, but we can't forget that even this dream is American, not Mexican.
